data.text: Draghi: We do not see risks of hoarding cash
Draghi: Bank lending survey shows credit is reaching non-financial sector of the economy. Our policy has been very effective
Draghi: The fragmentation is over. Credit has been growing constantly since 2014
Draghi: Inflation following baseline scenario, will take little longer than previously forecast to get to level below 2% but not much longer
Draghi: We are monitoring developments in inflation expectations very closely and stand ready to act
Draghi: There is no question about the will to act, the capacity to act, and the ability to do so
Draghi: For the time being the changes are not so substantial to warrant a decision to act. Our monetary policy is effective.
Introductory statement Mario Draghi to the press conference https://t.co/msrhU7bGZv
Draghi: Our programme is effective and we should focus on its implementation
Draghi: We didn't discuss extension of APP
Draghi: Fiscal policies should also support the economic recovery, while remaining in compliance with the fiscal rules of the EU
Draghi: Structural reforms are necessary in all euro area countries
Draghi: To reap full benefits from our measures other policy areas must contribute much more decisively at national and European level
Draghi: projections foresee annual HICP inflation at 0.2% in 2016, 1.2% in 2017 and 1.6% in 2018 (broadly unchanged)
Draghi: Sept projections: annual real GDP +1.7% in 2016 [June: +1.6%], +1.6% in 2017 [+1.7%], +1.6% in 2018
Draghi: if warranted, we will act by using all the instruments available within our mandate
Draghi: Governing Council will continue to monitor economic and financial market developments very closely
Draghi: while the available evidence suggests resilience of the euro area economy, the baseline scenario remains subject to downside risks
Draghi: monthly asset purchases of €80 billion are intended to run until the end of March 2017, or beyond, if necessary
Draghi: rates expected to stay at present or lower levels for an extended period of time, well past the horizon of asset purchases
